narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: My Japanese reading skill and writing skill have been enhanced.
I have boosted my Japanese reading and writing comprehension skills significantly. I can now comprehend simple news articles and novels with the aid of a dictionary.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: It's a great course! If the two wonderful senseis can collaborate with each other in their teaching styles, it would be even better.

Strengths: Professors are very helpful. Most course material is well prepared and easy to navigate. Weaknesses: It can sometimes be hard to practice speaking, especially if other students in class are quiet.
More focus could be given to improving students' speaking skills. Material was interesting to make up for the format being repetitive.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Get homework every day and need to study for Kanji quiz every for every class. The hw can get somewhat tedious but its a fun class overall.
Yes, I would definitely recommend this course to students who want to improve their Japanese from the intermediate level to the advanced level.
I would recommend this course to anyone interested in improving their Japanese.
